Electoral Division Health Profile for Mardyke, Cork City


Figure 1. Boundary Map for Mardyke, Cork City Electoral Division (Sources: OSI, Ireland; OpenStreetMap). Map style by Champs-Libres Coop., distributed under CC BY-SA.


Census 2022

CSO, Ireland (http://www.cso.ie)

A more detailed and print friendly pdf profile - with accompanying tables - is available here.

Note: This is the first time this profle has been compiled. While effort has been made to ensure this document is error free, it is possible that there may be some. Please email tomas.kelly@cso.ie if you observe any errors or inconsistencies with other CSO data.

1 Key Points

  • Mardyke, Cork City covers a total area of 0.4 square kilometers and has a population density of 2743.2 persons per square kilometer. The population density of Ireland as a whole is 73.3.

  • The Age Dependency Ratio of this Electoral Division (ED) is 15.1. This compares to 53.2 nationally. The Age Dependency Ratio is the amount of people outside of working age (0-14 and 65+) per 100 people of working age (15-64).

  • Mardyke, Cork City has a total of 1051 persons and 117 families living in private households.

  • There are a total of 74 persons aged 0-14 in this ED and 64 persons aged over 65.

  • There are a total of 250 persons living with a disability in this ED, representing 23.8 percent of the population. This compares with , 21.5, percent nationally

  • 12 people in this ED have bad or very bad general health. This represents 1.1 percent of the population. 1.7 percent of the population have bad or very bad general health nationally.

  • There are a total of 44 carers in this ED, representing 4.2 percent of the population. This compares with 5.8 percent of the population that are carers nationally.

  • 21.3 percent of this ED smoke tobacco products. 13.1 percent of people nationally smoke tobacco products

  • There are 33 short term unemployed and 25 long term unemployed people in this ED. These represent 3.4 and 2.6 percent of the population respectively.

  • 1.0 percent of the population of Mardyke, Cork City are unskilled. 3.1 percent of people in the state are unskilled.

  • 8.9 percent of those aged 15+ in this ED have a highest level of education of lower secondary or lower. This compares with 23 percent nationally.

  • 31.4 percent of families with children in this ED have lone parents. This stands at 24.8 nationally.

  • 40.3 percent of this ED were born outside Ireland (20 percent nationally).

  • Households rented from a Local Authority comprise 4.2 percent of households in this ED.This stands at 8.3 percent nationally
